Put a large #pot of water on high heat and add @salt{1/4%tsp}.

Cut the @Portobello Mushrooms{2} and @Chestnut Mushrooms{1} into 1cm thick slices.

Put a large #frying pan on high heat and add @oil{1%tbsp}. Fry the chestnut mushrooms in
batches and cook until golden.

> Tip: We cook the mushrooms in batches to make sure they fry and don't stew.

After ~{5%minutes} and once golden, season the mushrooms with @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good
grind of @black pepper{some}. Transfer to a #bowl and repeat this process with the
portobello mushrooms.

While the mushrooms are cooking, cut the @Echalion Shallot{1} in half through the root,
peel and chop into the smallest pieces you can. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}.

Pop the @Pappardelle{200%g} in the pot, cook for ~{7%minutes}, then drain.

Once the portobello mushrooms are ready, reduce the heat to low and add the shallot to the
pan. Cook for ~{3%minutes}, add the garlic, cook for ~{1%minute} more and then return
the cooked chestnut mushrooms to the mix.

Stir in the @Crème Fraîche{1}, warm gently and add @water{2%tbsp} to loosen up the sauce.
Check the seasoning and add @?salt{pinch} if needed and some ground @black pepper{}.

Drain the pasta and mix the mushroom sauce through the pasta. Pile the pasta into
#bowls and top with a handful of @Wild Rocket{1%handful} and a generous sprinkle of
@Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{3%tbsp}.